# ── Generated site ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Built by `mkdocs build` and `mkdocs gh-deploy`.  Never commit — the gh-pages
# branch holds the published site; the source tree holds only source.
site/

# ── Node ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Installed by `npm ci` / `npm install`.  Includes the bundled Chromium used by
# Mermaid CLI — ~150 MB, no need to track in git.
node_modules/

# ── Python ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.pyo
.venv/
venv/
env/
*.egg-info/
dist/
build/

# ── OS / editor noise ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# ── Local MkDocs temp files ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# mkdocs creates a temporary render config here during Mermaid pre-rendering.
docs/assets/mermaid/mermaid-render-config.json

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Things that look like they should be ignored but SHOULD be committed:
#
#   docs/assets/mermaid/*.png
#       Mermaid PNG cache.  Committing these means the CI job only re-renders
#       diagrams that have actually changed — mmdc/Chromium is not invoked at
#       all for cache hits.  Without the cache every build re-renders every
#       diagram, adding ~30-60 s per diagram on a cold runner.
#
#   docs/javascripts/vendor/mathjax/
#       Self-hosted MathJax library — a runtime asset served to browsers,
#       not a build tool.  Must be in the repo so the site works offline and
#       without any external CDN dependency.
#
#   docs/fonts/latinmodern-math.otf
#       Bundled math font used by WeasyPrint for PDF rendering.  A static
#       asset, not a build artifact.
#
#   package-lock.json
#       Pins the exact mmdc + Puppeteer + Chromium versions used by the hook.
#       Committing it ensures local dev and CI produce identical diagrams.
#
#   puppeteer.config.json
#       Puppeteer launch options for mmdc (--no-sandbox flags for CI).
#       Must be valid JSON — mmdc calls JSON.parse() on it directly.
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
